Bulletins.BulletinTitle: Sea/BI/Brem - On Tuesday, 9/25, Colman Dock elevators OOS for electrical work.
Bulletins.BulletinText: Colman Dock passenger elevators will be shut down for electrical work at the Seattle terminal at 12:15 a.m. Tuesday night and will reopen Wednesday morning at 4:30 a.m.  The stair lighting next to the elevators will also be turned off and the stairs will close for your safety.  The south side of the passenger level (Bremerton side) will also be blocked during this time. Passengers may access the terminal from the overhead walkway, the north stairs off Marion Street or the passenger ramp off Alaskan Way.

WaitTimes.WaitTimeNotes:
The first three morning departures have extremely heavy vehicle traffic, a 45-60 minute advance arrival suggested during this time. For other peak sailings, through about 10:00am, 45 minutes ahead is recommended. For non-peak travel, a minimum of 20 minutes ahead is suggested.

Passengers should arrive at least 15 minutes prior to sailing.

Bulletins.BulletinTitle: Faunt/Va/SW-Construction Activities at Fauntleroy
Bulletins.BulletinText: Construction activities continue on King County's Barton Pump Station Upgrade Project adjacent to the Fauntleroy terminal. Beginning this week customers will notice more construction equipment and activity, with flaggers directing construction traffic in and out of the project site between 7 a.m. and 5:30 p.m. Monday through Friday. Work will be coordinated with busy ferry travel times. For more information please contact Kristine Cramer at kristine.cramer@kingcounty.gov or 206-263-3184, or call the 24-hour project hotline at 206-296-2999.
